      "role": "user",
      "content": "i cant stop thinking about how none of this actually matters. like, if you look at the scale of the universe, everything we do is just a tiny blip of noise that’s gonna be deleted eventually. it feels like we're just pretending there's a point to any of this struggle. is it just me or is the whole concept of \"living\" kind of a losing battle?",
